Item 5.02 Departure of Directors or Certain Officers; Election of Directors; Appointment of Certain Officers; Compensatory Arrangements of Certain Officers.
(d) On September 15, 2010, Erica Farber was re-appointed to the Board of Directors of Arbitron Inc. (the "Company") to serve until the next annual meeting of stockholders of the Company, or until her earlier death, resignation or removal. Additional information about Ms. Farber is included in the Companys press release issued on September 15, 2010, which is attached as Exhibit 99.1 to this Current Report on Form 8-K and incorporated herein by reference. Ms. Farber will participate in the Companys previously disclosed Non-Employee Director Incentive Program. In connection with joining the Companys Board of Directors, on September 15, 2010, Ms. Farber received a one-time grant of 4,500 deferred stock units, which deferred stock units will vest in three equal installments of 1,500 deferred stock units over a three-year period and will be payable no sooner than six months following Ms. Farbers termination of service as a director of the Company. The award is in the form of the Companys standard 2008 Equity Compensation Plan Director Deferred Stock Unit Agreement - Initial Grant under the Arbitron Inc. 2008 Equity Compensation Plan, which will be filed as an exhibit to the Companys Form 10-Q for the quarter ended September 30, 2010.
